[DEFAULT]
Flask template for the ISO 27001 Manager application.

This application provides a comprehensive ISMS (Information Security Management System)
covering all ISO 27001:2022 requirements including:

- All 93 Annex A controls across 4 domains (Organizational, People, Physical, Technological)
- ISO Clauses 4-10 compliance tracking
- Risk assessment and treatment
- Asset management with classification
- Incident management
- Policy and document version control
- Internal audit management with findings and non-conformities
- Statement of Applicability (SoA)
- Supplier security assessments
- KPI tracking and reporting
- User management with role-based access control
- Two-factor authentication (TOTP)
- Full audit trail logging
- CSV export for all modules


QUICK START (Development):
    cp .env.example .env
    python -m venv venv
    source venv/bin/activate
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    python run.py
    # Open http://localhost:5000
    # Default credentials: admin / Admin@ISO27001!2024

PRODUCTION (Docker):
    cp .env.example .env
    # Edit .env with production values
    docker-compose up -d

DEFAULT ACCOUNTS:
    admin    / Admin@ISO27001!2024  (full access)
    manager  / Manager@ISO27001!2024
    auditor  / Auditor@ISO27001!2024
    user     / User@ISO27001!2024

TECH STACK:
    Flask 3.x, SQLAlchemy 2.x, Bootstrap 5.3, AdminLTE 4
    SQLite (dev) / PostgreSQL (prod)
    TOTP 2FA via pyotp
    Gunicorn + Nginx (production)
    Chart.js for visualizations
